				</div>
				<div class="commission-item">
					<div class="commission-icon">
						<img src="/images/affiliate/custom-quotes-icon.svg" alt="Custom Quotes icon" title="Custom Quotes icon" />
					</div>
					<p class="commission-rate">10% commission</p>
					<p>On Perpetual Licenses</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section id="audience">
		<div class="affiliate-main">
			<h2>Who might find this interesting?</h2>
			<div class="audience-cards">
				<div class="audience-card">
					<div class="audience-icon">
						<img
							src="/images/affiliate/content-creators-icon.svg"
							alt="Content Creators icon"
							title="Content Creators icon"
						/>
					</div>
					<h3>Content Creators</h3>
					<p>
						Turn your tutorials into a reliable revenue stream. Whether you produce YouTube content or professional
						courses, monetize your expertise
					</p>
					<a
						href="https://affiliates.thingsboard.io/signup/"
						class="btn-outline"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer"
						>Earn from your traffic<span class="visually-hidden">
							as a Content Creator with ThingsBoard Affiliate Program</span
						></a
					>
				</div>
				<div class="audience-card">
					<div class="audience-icon">
						<img src="/images/affiliate/consultants-icon.svg" alt="IoT Consultants icon" title="IoT Consultants icon" />
					</div>
					<h3>IoT Consultants</h3>
					<p>Generate steady passive income by recommending a production-ready IoT platform your clients can trust</p>
					<a
						href="https://affiliates.thingsboard.io/signup/"
						class="btn-outline"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer"
						>Build passive income<span class="visually-hidden">
							as an IoT Consultant with ThingsBoard Affiliate Program</span
						></a
					>
				</div>
				<div class="audience-card">
					<div class="audience-icon">
						<img
							src="/images/affiliate/hardware-manufacturers-icon.svg"
							alt="Hardware Manufacturers icon"
							title="Hardware Manufacturers icon"
						/>
					</div>
					<h3>Hardware Manufacturers</h3>
					<p>
						Provide your customers with a world-class visualization layer. Recommend ThingsBoard for your sensors and
						gateways to deliver a complete, ready-to-use IoT solution
					</p>
					<a
						href="https://affiliates.thingsboard.io/signup/"
						class="btn-outline"
						target="_blank"
						rel="noopener noreferrer"
						>Monetize your hardware<span class="visually-hidden">
							as a Hardware Manufacturer with ThingsBoard Affiliate Program</span
						></a
					>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section id="success">
		<div class="affiliate-main">
			<div class="success-content">
				<div class="success-text">
					<div class="success-tag">
						<img src="/images/affiliate/partner-toolkit-icon.svg" alt="Toolkit icon" title="Partner Toolkit icon" />
						<span>Partner Toolkit</span>
					</div>
					<h2>We set you up <span class="blue-text">for success</span></h2>
					<p class="success-description">
						We don't just give you a link. We will provide you with a comprehensive marketing arsenal designed to move
						your audience through the funnel and maximize your conversion rates
					</p>
					<div class="success-list">
						<div class="success-item">
							<div class="success-item-icon">
								<img
									src="/images/affiliate/plug-and-play-icon.svg"
									alt="Plug and Play icon"
									title="Plug and Play icon"
								/>
							</div>
							<div class="success-item-content">
								<h3>Plug-and-Play Creative Assets</h3>
								<p>
									Access professional banners, social media templates, and high-converting copy to launch your campaigns
									quickly
								</p>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="success-item">
							<div class="success-item-icon">
								<img
									src="/images/affiliate/partner-playbook-icon.svg"
									alt="Playbook icon"
									title="Affiliate Partner Playbook icon"
								/>
							</div>
							<div class="success-item-content">
								<h3>Affiliate Partner Playbook</h3>
								<p>Everything you need to know: from key value propositions to detailed compensation models</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="success-image">
					<img src="/images/affiliate/folders.webp" alt="Partner toolkit folders" title="Partner toolkit folders" />
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section id="faq">
		<div class="affiliate-main">
			<h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="faq-list">
				<div class="faq-item">
					<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
						<h3>Who can become a ThingsBoard affiliate?</h3>
						<Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="faq-arrow" size={24} />
					</button>
					<div class="faq-answer">
						<p>
							We welcome anyone with a relevant audience or professional network in the IoT space. This includes tech
							bloggers, YouTubers, IoT consultants, system integrators, and hardware manufacturers. If you create
							content or provide solutions that help businesses connect and manage their devices, you are a perfect fit
							for our program.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
						<h3>How is the commission calculated?</h3>
						<Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="faq-arrow" size={24} />
					</button>
					<div class="faq-answer">
						<p>
							Commission is calculated as a percentage of the actual payment made by the customer. You receive:<br /><b
								>30%</b
							> for Public Cloud and Self-managed subscriptions (recurring for 12 months);<br /><b>15%</b> for Private Cloud
							subscriptions (recurring for 12 months);<br /><b>10%</b> for Perpetual Licenses and Enterprise contracts (one-time).
							Earnings are credited to your FirstPromoter account immediately after the client's payment is confirmed.<br
							/><br /><i
								>Example: For a client referred to the "Pilot" plan on the Public Cloud, you will receive a commission
								of $44.70 per month. This equates to a total annual commission of $536.40 from a single client.</i
							>
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
						<h3>Can I earn rewards for referring free users?</h3>
						<Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="faq-arrow" size={24} />
					</button>
					<div class="faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes! We value community growth. You can earn a $100 bonus for every 100 verified users who sign up for our
							Public Cloud Free Subscription plan through your unique affiliate link. This allows you to monetize your
							reach even if your audience isn't ready for a paid plan yet.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
						<h3>What is the payout schedule?</h3>
						<Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="faq-arrow" size={24} />
					</button>
					<div class="faq-answer">
						<p>
							Commissions are paid monthly. We pay out all earned commissions once a month, regardless of the amount,
							ensuring you receive your rewards consistently.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
						<h3>How does tracking and attribution work technically?</h3>
						<Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="faq-arrow" size={24} />
					</button>
					<div class="faq-answer">
						<p>
							When a user clicks your link, your Promoter ID is automatically linked to their profile as soon as they
							sign up for our Cloud/License Portal or submit a "Contact Us" request. We use FirstPromoter to accurately
							track commissions and process payouts via PayPal or Wise. Most importantly, we protect your leads with a
							first-touch attribution model: the partner who originally introduced the user earns the commission, not
							the one whose link was clicked last before the purchase.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
						<h3>What is the recommended roadmap for success?</h3>
						<Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="faq-arrow" size={24} />
					</button>
					<div class="faq-answer">
						<p>
							1. Join: Sign up to get your unique affiliate link.<br />2. Learn: Download the 'Playbook' from our
							Partner Toolkit to master the value proposition.<br />3. Create: Publish a tutorial, case study, or
							comparison article featuring ThingsBoard.<br />4. Distribute: Share it with your audience on LinkedIn,
							YouTube, or your blog.<br />5. Earn: Track your clicks in FirstPromoter and receive monthly payouts.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
						<h3>What are the key program concepts I should know?</h3>
						<Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="faq-arrow" size={24} />
					</button>
					<div class="faq-answer">
						<p>
							<b>First-Touch Attribution:</b> You get the credit if you are the first to refer a user, protecting your leads
							regardless of future clicks.<br /><b>90-Day Cookie:</b> If a user clicks your link and converts within 3 months,
							you earn the commission.<br /><b>Net-30 Payouts:</b> We process payments once a month for the previous month's
							approved earnings.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
						<h3>What marketing methods are prohibited?</h3>
						<Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="faq-arrow" size={24} />
					</button>
					<div class="faq-answer">
						<p>
							To protect our brand, we prohibit 'Brand Bidding' (running ads on keywords like 'ThingsBoard') and
							unsolicited spam. We highly encourage organic content, case studies, and direct consulting.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
						<h3>What is the difference between the subscription plans?</h3>
						<Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="faq-arrow" size={24} />
					</button>
					<div class="faq-answer">
						<p>
							<a href="/products/paas/">Public Cloud</a> is a ready-to-use SaaS solution hosted by us. <a
								href="/products/thingsboard-pe/">Self-managed (Professional Edition)</a
							> allows customers to install the platform on their own servers or cloud for full control. <a
								href="/pricing/?product=thingsboard-private-cloud">Private Cloud</a
							> is a dedicated instance managed by our team for high-load enterprise projects. <a
								href="/pricing/?product=thingsboard-pe&solution=pe-perpetual">Perpetual Licenses</a
							> are a one-time purchase option for self-hosted deployments.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="faq-item">
					<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">
						<h3>I have more questions. Who should I contact?</h3>
						<Icon name="tabler:chevron-down" class="faq-arrow" size={24} />
					</button>
					<div class="faq-answer">
						<p>
							If you have specific questions or need assistance, please contact our partner team directly at <a
								href="mailto:affiliates@thingsboard.io">affiliates@thingsboard.io</a
							>. We are here to help you succeed!
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section id="cta">
		<div class="affiliate-main">
			<div class="cta-card">
				<h2>Ready to become a ThingsBoard affiliate?</h2>
				<p>Join 1,000+ experts building on the world's most popular IoT platform.</p>
				<a
					href="https://affiliates.thingsboard.io/signup/"
					class="btn-primary"
					target="_blank"
					rel="noopener noreferrer"
				>
					Become a Partner
					<Icon name="tabler:chevron-right" />
					<span class="visually-hidden">Become a ThingsBoard Affiliate Partner</span>
				</a>
				<p class="cta-note">Free to start. No minimum audience size required</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
	document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
		const slider = document.getElementById('profitSlider') as HTMLInputElement | null;
		const profitAmount = document.getElementById('profitAmount');
		const customerCount = document.getElementById('customerCount');
		const commissionPerCustomer = 536;

		function updateSlider() {
			if (!slider || !profitAmount || !customerCount) return;
			const customers = parseInt(slider.value);
			const percent = ((customers - 1) / 99) * 100;
			const primaryColor = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--color-primary').trim();
			const trackColor = getComputedStyle(document.documentElement).getPropertyValue('--color-border').trim();
			slider.style.background =
				'linear-gradient(to right, ' +
				primaryColor +
				' 0%, ' +
				primaryColor +
				' ' +
				percent +
				'%, ' +
				trackColor +
				' ' +
				percent +
				'%, ' +
				trackColor +
				' 100%)';
			customerCount.textContent = String(customers);
			const profit = customers * commissionPerCustomer;
			profitAmount.textContent = '$' + profit.toLocaleString().replace(/,/g, ' ');
		}

		if (slider) {
			slider.addEventListener('input', updateSlider);
			updateSlider();

			// Re-read CSS variables when theme changes
			const observer = new MutationObserver((mutations) => {
				for (const m of mutations) {
					if (m.attributeName === 'data-theme') {
						updateSlider();
					}
				}
			});
			observer.observe(document.documentElement, { attributes: true });
		}

		const faqQuestions = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-question');

		faqQuestions.forEach((question) => {
			question.addEventListener('click', () => {
				const item = question.parentElement;
				if (!item) return;
				const isActive = item.classList.contains('active');

				if (isActive) {
					item.classList.remove('active');
					question.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
				} else {
					item.classList.add('active');
					question.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
				}
			});
		});

		const chartCard = document.querySelector('.chart-card');
		if (chartCard) {
			const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
				function (entries) {
					entries.forEach(function (entry) {
						if (entry.isIntersecting) {
							entry.target.classList.add('animated');
							observer.unobserve(entry.target);
						}
					});
				},
				{ threshold: 0.3 }
			);

			observer.observe(chartCard);
		}
	});
</script>

<style lang="scss">
	// Page surface color — applied to the page id (still on <html>).
	:global(#affiliate),
	:global(#affiliate body) {
		background-color: var(--color-bg-surface);
	}

	// Make body the positioning context for the absolutely-positioned
	// background pattern below. Body is in normal flow, so this affects
	// nothing visually — but it gives the .affiliate-bg-pattern a stable
	// containing block that exists in the DOM (unlike a pseudo-element on
	// <html>, which had ambiguous painting behavior on the staging deploy).
	:global(#affiliate body) {
		position: relative;
	}

	.affiliate-bg-pattern {
		position: absolute;
		top: 0;
		left: 0;
		width: 100%;
		height: 1100px;
		background-image: url('/images/affiliate/background.svg');
		background-size: cover;
		background-position: top center;
		background-repeat: no-repeat;
		z-index: 0;
		pointer-events: none;
		-webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, black 70%, transparent 100%);
		mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, black 70%, transparent 100%);

		// Hidden in dark mode (matches the previous behavior).
		:global([data-theme='dark']) & {
			display: none;
		}
	}

	// Header appearance (transparent → opaque on hover/scroll) is now provided
	// by the `transparent-hover` header variant — see HeaderContent.astro.

	.visually-hidden {
		position: absolute;
		width: 1px;
		height: 1px;
		padding: 0;
		margin: -1px;
		overflow: hidden;
		clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
		white-space: nowrap;
		border: 0;
	}

	section {
		background-color: transparent;
		position: relative;
	}

	.affiliate-main {
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1;
		max-width: 1080px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 20px;
	}

	.blue-text {
		color: var(--color-primary);
	}

	// ── Buttons ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

	.btn-primary {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: flex-start;
		gap: 8px;
		min-width: 200px;
		height: 48px;
		background: var(--color-primary);
		border-radius: 6px;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 500;
		color: white;
		text-decoration: none;
		padding: 0 16px 0 24px;
		box-shadow: 0 4px 16px color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-primary) 24%, transparent);
		transition:
			background 0.3s ease,
			box-shadow 0.3s ease,
			color 0.3s ease;
		position: relative;
		overflow: hidden;

		&:hover {
			background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-primary) 85%, black);
			color: white;
			text-decoration: none;
			box-shadow: 0 6px 20px color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-primary) 32%, transparent);

			:global(svg) {
				transform: translateX(5px);
			}
		}

		:global(svg) {
			width: 20px;
			height: 20px;
			flex-shrink: 0;
			transition: transform 0.3s ease;
		}
	}

	.btn-outline {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		min-width: 200px;
		height: 48px;
		background: var(--color-primary);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-primary);
		border-radius: 6px;
		font-size: 16px;
		font-weight: 500;
		color: white;
		text-decoration: none;
		padding: 16px;
		transition:
			background 0.3s ease,
